This paper is about detecting jamming attacks in wireless communication, which is a topic related to network security and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses machine learning algorithms for jamming detection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of statistical techniques and probability analysis, which could be classified under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with security issues in wireless communication, which could be classified under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
